-- South African Coal Prices Have Second Weekly Advance This Month
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-02-27T10:12:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-27/south-african-coal-prices-have-second-weekly-advance-this-month.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, rose for a second week.  Prices (CLSPSARB)  added $1.27, or 1.2 percent, to $106.11 a metric ton
in the week ended Feb. 24, according to IHS McCloskey data on
Bloomberg. That’s the highest level since Jan. 27.  The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  